Results</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">MIDLAND, MI, </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">October&#160;22, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;-- Chemical Financial Corporation (NASDAQ:CHFC) today announced </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;">2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">third quarter</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;net income of </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$16.8 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$0.51</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per diluted share, compared to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;net income of </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$15.0 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$0.53</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per diluted share, and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;net income of </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$16.2 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$0.54</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per diluted share. For the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">nine months ended September 30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, net income was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$46.8 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$1.51</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per diluted share, compared to net income for the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">nine months ended September 30, 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$42.4 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$1.53</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per diluted share. The declines in diluted per share earnings for the three and nine months ended September 30, 2014 were attributable to the higher number of outstanding shares resulting from the Corporation's September 2013 and June 2014 common equity offerings and nonrecurring transaction-related expenses incurred during 2014.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">Nonrecurring transaction-related expenses attributable to the pending acquisition of Northwestern Bancorp, Inc. ("Northwestern") were </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$1.3 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$2.2 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;for the three and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">nine months ended September 30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, respectively. Regulatory approval has been received and the Corporation expects to complete the acquisition on October 31, 2014, subject to the satisfaction of customary closing conditions.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">Excluding nonrecurring transaction-related expenses, net income in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;was $17.6 million, or $0.53 per diluted share, up 17% over net income of $15.0 million in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#8220;Chemical Financial enjoyed another quarter of strong earnings, as continued strength in the Michigan economy and solid performance across our banking franchise allowed us to post double-digit percentage growth in net income before the impact of nonrecurring transaction-related expenses,&#8221; noted David B. Ramaker, Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of Chemical Financial Corporation. &#8220;Michigan's improving economy, coupled with competitive share gains across our market footprint, were the primary drivers of this quarter&#8217;s results, enabling us to post double digit loan growth. Margins were stable and credit quality continued to improve.&#8221;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">"With the receipt of regulatory approval for our previously announced acquisition of Northwestern Bancorp, Inc., the holding company for Northwestern Bank, we anticipate closing the acquisition on October 31, 2014, putting our surplus capital to work. We continue to believe our strategic partnership with Northwestern and its 25 locations across 11 northwestern Michigan counties will provide a compelling choice for the state's residents and businesses," added Ramaker.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">Net income, excluding nonrecurring transaction-related expenses, in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;was 17% </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">higher</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;than the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;due to a combination of higher net interest income, higher noninterest income and a lower provision for loan losses, which were partially offset by higher operating expenses. Net income, excluding nonrecurring transaction-related expenses, in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;was 5.6% </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">higher</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;than the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">second quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, with the increase primarily attributable to higher net interest income.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">The Corporation's return on average assets was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">1.04%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;during the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, compared to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">1.00%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">1.04%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">second quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. The Corporation's return on average shareholders' equity was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">8.4%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, compared to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">9.6%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">9.1%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">second quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. The decreases in return on average shareholders' equity in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, compared to both the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">second quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, was primarily attributable to increases in shareholders' equity resulting from the Corporation's September 2013 and June 2014 common equity offerings and nonrecurring transaction-related expenses. Nonrecurring transaction-related expenses in the third quarter of 2014 reduced the Corporation's return on average assets by 5 basis points and return on average shareholders' equity by 42 basis points.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">Net interest income was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$53.1 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$3.8 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">7.7%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">higher</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;than the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$1.6 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">3.1%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">higher</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;than the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">second quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. The increase in net interest income in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;over the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;was largely attributable to the positive impact of loan growth of $518 million, or 11.5%, during the twelve months ended </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">September&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. The increase in net interest income in </font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">1</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sEFD195EFE0D9B9E0853DB1A27601A4FD"></a><div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;over the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">second quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;was also largely attributable to the positive impact of loan growth, with average loan balances up $139 million, or 2.9%, in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;over the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">second quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">The net interest margin (on a tax-equivalent basis) was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">3.59%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, compared to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">3.58%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">3.59%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">second quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. The positive impact on the net interest margin attributable to loan growth during the three and twelve months ended </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">September&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;was offset by a reduction in the average yield on the loan portfolio. The average yield on the loan portfolio was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">4.23%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, compared to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">4.44%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">4.26%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">second quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. The average yield of the investment securities portfolio was 2.19% in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, compared to 2.05% in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and 2.13% in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">second quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. Modest changes in the mix of customer deposits and the repricing of matured customer certificates of deposit resulted in the Corporation's average cost of funds declining to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">0.25%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;from </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">0.32%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">third quarter of 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. The increase in total deposits during the third quarter of 2014 was largely attributable to a seasonal increase in municipal customer deposits. The Corporation experienced an increase in total deposits of $241 million, or 4.6%, during the twelve months ended </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">September&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">At </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, the Corporation's tangible equity to assets ratio and total risk-based capital ratio were </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">10.5%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">15.0%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, respectively, compared to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">11.0%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">15.3%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, respectively, at </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">June&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">8.9%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">14.2%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, respectively, at </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. The increases in the Corporation's capital ratios at </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, compared to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, were largely attributable to the Corporation&#8217;s June 2014 public offering of common stock. At </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, the Corporation's book value was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$24.47</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per share, compared to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$24.22</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per share at </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">June&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$22.61</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per share at </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. At </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, the Corporation's tangible book value was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$20.68</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per share, compared to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$20.42</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per share at </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">June&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">$18.36</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;per share at </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2013</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">This press release contains references to financial measures which are not defined in generally accepted accounting principles ("GAAP"). Such non-GAAP financial measures include the Corporation's tangible equity to assets ratio, presentation of net interest income on a fully taxable equivalent basis (FTE) and information presented excluding nonrecurring transaction-related expenses, including net income, diluted earnings per share, return on average assets, return on average shareholders' equity and operating expenses. These non-GAAP financial measures have been included as the Corporation believes they are helpful for investors to analyze and evaluate the Corporation's financial condition.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">Chemical Financial Corporation will host a conference call to discuss its </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">third quarter</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;">2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;operating results on Thursday, October&#160;23, 2014 at 11:00 a.m. EDT. Anyone interested may access the conference call on a live basis by dialing toll-free at 1-800-390-5360 and entering 7350138 for the conference ID. The call will also be broadcast live over the Internet hosted at Chemical Financial Corporation's website at </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;text-decoration:underline;">www.chemicalbankmi.com</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">&#32;under the "Investor Info" section.&#160;A copy of the slide-show presentation and an audio replay of the call will remain available on Chemical Financial Corporation's website for at least 14 days.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">Chemical Financial Corporation is the second largest banking company headquartered and operating branch offices in Michigan. The Corporation operates through a single subsidiary bank, Chemical Bank, with 157 banking offices spread over 38 counties in Michigan. At </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">, the Corporation had total assets of </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$6.6 billion</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">. Chemical Financial Corporation's common stock trades on The NASDAQ Stock Market under the symbol CHFC and is one of the issues comprising The NASDAQ Global Select Market. More information about the Corporation is available by visiting the investor relations section of its website at www.chemicalbankmi.com.</font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">3</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sEFD195EFE0D9B9E0853DB1A27601A4FD"></a><div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:10px;padding-top:10px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Forward-Looking Statements</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:9px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">This press release contains forward-looking statements that are based on management's beliefs, assumptions, current expectations, estimates and projections about the financial services industry, the economy and Chemical Financial Corporation (Corporation). These statements are not guarantees of future performance and involve certain risks, uncertainties and assumptions ("risk factors") that are difficult to predict with regard to timing, extent, likelihood and degree of occurrence. Therefore, actual results and outcomes may materially differ from what may be expressed or forecasted in such forward-looking statements. The Corporation undertakes no obligation to update, amend or clarify forward-looking statements, whether as a result of new information, future events or otherwise.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:9px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">This press release may contain forward-looking statements regarding the Corporation's outlook or expectations with respect to the planned acquisition of Northwestern Bancorp, Inc. (Northwestern), the expected costs to be incurred in connection with the acquisition, Northwestern&#8217;s future performance and consequences of its integration into the Corporation and the impact of the transaction on the Corporation&#8217;s future performance.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:9px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Risk factors relating to both the transaction and the integration of Northwestern into the Corporation after closing include, without limitation:</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:8px;text-align:justify;padding-left:18px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The impact of the completion of the transaction on the Corporation's financial statements will be affected by the timing of the transaction, including in particular the ability to complete the acquisition in the fourth quarter of 2014.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:8px;text-align:justify;padding-left:18px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The transaction may be more expensive to complete and the anticipated benefits, including anticipated cost savings and strategic gains, may be significantly harder or take longer to achieve than expected or may not be achieved in their entirety as a result of unexpected factors or events.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:8px;text-align:justify;padding-left:18px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The integration of Northwestern's business and operations into the Corporation, which will include conversion of Northwestern's operating systems and procedures, may take longer than anticipated or be more costly than anticipated or have unanticipated adverse results relating to Northwestern's or the Corporation's existing businesses.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:12px;text-align:justify;padding-left:18px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The Corporation's ability to achieve anticipated results from the transaction is dependent on the state of the economic and financial markets going forward. Specifically, the Corporation may incur more credit losses from Northwestern&#8217;s loan portfolio than expected and deposit attrition may be greater than expected.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:12px;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Risk factors also include, but are not limited to, the risk factors described under "Risk Factors" (including the risk factors under the heading "Risk Factors - Risks Related to the Pending Merger with Northwestern") in the Corporation's Prospectus Supplement, dated June 19, 2014, and in Item&#160;1A of the Corporation&#8217;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&#160;31, 2013. These and other factors are representative of the risk factors that may emerge and could cause a difference between an ultimate actual outcome and a preceding forward-looking statement.</font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">4</font></div></div><hr
